Articles.Content:
Hello,

I have recently upgraded my System and now I tried getting KSP running again. I tried starting the game, but it crashes on the startup loading screen.

I am running the 64bit version on ubuntu 64bit. I start KSP by running this ksp.sh:

Spoiler

#!/bin/sh  


export LC_ALL=C  
export LD_PRELOAD="libpthread.so.0 libGL.so.1"  
export __GL_THREADED_OPTIMIZATIONS=1  
exec taskset -c 2-3 ./KSP.x86_64

Hi matko1990, does an unmodded copy of KSP work for you if you start it via the KSP.x86_64 directly ?

I see you have ckan on the desktop, and as your error shows a missing steamclient.so I'm assuming KSP is in your Steam ~/.steam/steamapps/common/ folder.

I'm pretty sure that ckan does not change directory into the KSP folder before trying to run it, this causes KSP to look for some files local to the current working directory, in this case ~/Desktop/ckan/

The Steam version tries to load the steamclient.so for the Steam overlay, but won't be able to find it unless the working directory is the Kerbal Space Program folder.

So you should be able to solve this by putting ckan in the Kerbal Space Program folder and running it from there, or possibly by making a shortcut to the ckan.exe that sets the KSP folder as the working directory.

Or by cd'ing in to the KSP folder in your script, then calling ckan with "mono ~/Desktop/ckan/ckan.exe"
